  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 1 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 5 high, 5 medium, 29 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Poznań-Ławica (POZ/EPPO); plus 2 other bases. 5 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is fog / freezing fog, mist and RVR limitations  — most notably around London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Poznań-Ławica (POZ/EPPO). Network hotspots: Keflavik (KEF/BIKF). Primary drivers: low cloud base, thunderstorm / convective risk and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 9 airports changed status, led by Oslo-Gardermoen (OSL/ENGM), Stavanger Airport, Sola (SVG/ENZV), Tromsø Airport, Langnes (TOS/ENTC) and 6 others.",
